  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Contact East 2026";
  schema:description """
	Contact East happens in Atlantic Canada every 2 years and this year it is in Saint John at Imperial Theatre. Contact East is a conference for Presenters, Artists and Agents to get together and for the Artists to showcase their talent for consideration for tours in Atlantic Canada. The Artists are given 15-20 minutes each to sing, dance, act, juggle, etc. and to enlist Presenters, like Imperial Theatre, to bring them to their theatre.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>We want to invite you to come and check out the Artists, along with us and presenters from NB, NS, PEI and Newfoundland & Labrador. Afterwards we plan to send out a short survey so you can give us your feedback on what you've seen. Your opinion matters. The Showcases are in 2+ hour slots but you don't have to stay the whole time. We do, it's our job, but you can leave in between performances if you need to. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://contacteast.ca/showcase/showcasing/\"> Learn more about the Showcasing Artists</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Wednesday, April 8 from 2:30-4:30pm: Showcase #1</h2><ul><li>Natasha Blackwood</li><li>Tanya Davis – Mass for Shut-Outs</li><li>Little Misty</li><li>Sophie Lukacs</li><li>Mat Hughes</li></ul><span><br/></span><h2>Wednesday, April 8 from 7:30-10:15pm: Showcase #2</h2><ul><li>Logan Richard</li><li>Tyler Hache</li><li>Durham County Poets</li><li>Daniel James McFadyen</li><li>John Muirhead</li></ul><span><br/></span><h2>Thursday, April 9 from 2:45-5:00pm: Showcase #3</h2><ul><li>Tocani</li><li>Rube & Rake</li><li>Zuppa</li><li>Jing Xia</li><li>Corpuscule Danse</li></ul><span><br/></span><h2>Thursday, April 9 from 8:00-10:00pm: Showcase #4</h2><ul><li>Oktopus</li><li>The Dusty Halos</li><li>HEIST</li></ul><span><br/></span><h2>Friday, April 10 from 1:30-3:30pm: Showcase #5</h2><ul><li>Tina Leon</li><li>Aquakultre</li><li>Pony Girl</li><li>Justin Fancy</li><li>Abigail Lapell</li></ul>
""";
