<http://www.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/event/24201AQBJSCTMKBQRHSLCPQSBDTRMBNBT>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Music of the Night: The Concert Tour";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">Music of the Night: The Concert Tour</span><span><br/></span>A Concert Celebration of Andrew Lloyd Webber's Greatest Hits<span><br/></span>Presented by Sound the Alarm: Music/Theatre<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This concert celebration of Andrew Lloyd Webber comes to Saint John having toured across Canada to sold out audiences from Victoria to Halifax! With a live band and many incredible and celebrated singers, we welcome you to experience this concert of Andrew Lloyd Webber’s most iconic theatrical music - including selections from Phantom of the Opera, Evita, Cats, Jesus Christ Superstar, Sunset Blvd, and more!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Production Information & Promo Video: <a target=\"_top\" href=\"http:// www.musicofthenight.live\"> www.musicofthenight.live</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Reviews:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">\"What an amazing show!!! Wonderful mix of songs represented!  Just amazing!!!  Get your tickets now!!!  Should not miss this amazing show!” Melanie Ngai, Vancouver, BC<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>\"This was very entertaining, the cast had unbelievable voices, and what a wonderful way to spend a Sunday afternoon\" Angela Carter, Barrie, ON<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>\"this very professional and capable cast – made up of seasoned singers ... never ceased to amaze us with a string of hits that made famous the brilliant Andrew Lloyd Webber.  The artists are versatile, play very well and have voices to spare... They all impressed me. It’s a very solid cast.\"  Review:  atuvu.ca (Montreal)</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Regarding Sound the Alarm's Special Price Points:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><ul><li>Indigenous Community: In response to the Calls to Action from the Truth and Reconciliation Commission of Canada, Sound the Alarm is offering modest discounted rates to the Indigenous Community as a small gesture.</li></ul><span><br/></span><ul><li>Arts Workers: Sound the Alarm considers this to include anyone working, or pursuing a life in the arts in any capacity (admin or artist etc).</li></ul><span><br/></span><ul><li>Economy Relief: Sound the Alarm understands the economy is tricky at present, so we offer this price to anyone who feels they need a lower price.  If this is not the case for you, we ask that you honour the standard pricing to help Sound the Alarm, a registered charity, through this economy in return.</li></ul><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">WARNING:  This production includes the use of haze, fog and some flashing lights.</span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-04-02T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/files/54d38f25-6b19-477d-aafb-012d85f6ac41.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/location/201AGBHDRLQHNHPHKKMPKLGPMDRDTDMVL>;
